3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"MEXC calculates funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC based on the premium/discount between the perpetual price and mark price. The funding rate is capped at ±0.75% per interval with a typical range of ±0.01%. When positive, long positions pay shorts; when negative, shorts pay longs. Zero maker fees significantly reduce the cost basis for maintaining neutral delta hedges."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","MEME","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"MEME token's high volatility and retail sentiment creates frequent funding rate imbalances on MEXC, particularly during meme coin rallies. The smaller order book depth means funding rates can diverge more significantly from other exchanges, creating cross-exchange arbitrage opportunities. MEXC's first-to-list advantage often results in unique funding rate patterns not available elsewhere."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"MEME/USDT funding rates on MEXC have shown extreme volatility ranging from -2.25% to +2.25% during major meme coin cycles. Positive funding dominates during retail FOMO periods, often exceeding +0.3% per 8-hour interval. Negative funding typically occurs during broader market downturns when leveraged longs get liquidated. The pattern shows strong correlation with social media sentiment and broader meme coin sector performance."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"MEXC's zero maker fees create favorable conditions for delta-neutral funding rate collection strategies. Cross-exchange arbitrage opportunities frequently arise due to MEXC's thinner liquidity compared to Binance or OKX. The 8-hour funding interval allows for three daily collection periods, though positions must be held through each settlement time. Traders can exploit funding rate differences by going long on MEXC when funding is negative while shorting on exchanges with positive rates."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"MEXC's questionable volume reporting raises concerns about actual liquidity depth during volatile periods. The exchange's limited regulatory compliance creates counterparty risk that must be factored into position sizing. Thin order books can result in significant slippage when adjusting hedge positions, particularly during meme coin volatility spikes. Auto-deleveraging risk increases during extreme market moves due to the concentrated retail user base and high leverage usage."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"What makes MEXC's MEME/USDT funding rates different from other exchanges?","answer":"MEXC often lists MEME perpetuals before major exchanges, creating unique funding rate dynamics. The zero maker fee structure and smaller order books can lead to more extreme funding rate deviations, especially during meme coin hype cycles."},{"question":"How reliable are MEXC's funding rate payments for MEME/USDT?","answer":"MEXC processes funding payments reliably every 8 hours, though the exchange's regulatory uncertainties create counterparty risk. Users should monitor exchange health and avoid concentrating large positions during volatile periods."},{"question":"Can I hedge MEXC MEME positions on other exchanges?","answer":"Yes, but MEME perpetuals may not be available on all major exchanges due to MEXC's first-to-list strategy. Cross-exchange hedging opportunities depend on which other venues have listed MEME perpetuals and their relative liquidity."},{"question":"What's the maximum funding rate for MEME/USDT on MEXC?","answer":"MEXC caps funding rates at ±0.75% per 8-hour interval (±2.25% daily). During extreme meme coin volatility, rates often hit these caps, creating predictable arbitrage opportunities for traders positioned appropriately."}]}]
